    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201122/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-22"><time>2020-11-22</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Eu&#xAD;nice Quek&#xD;&#xA;Food Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent</span>
    </section>

    <p>School’s out, time to hunt down pit stops to fuel up for the year-end hol­i­days. You are in luck as many new themed cafes now abound. Head to the pop-up Juras­sic World Cafe at Ion Sky with lit­tle dino lovers or run free with the kids at the play­ground next to the two­day-old The Singapura Aerospace Club at Sele­tar Aerospace Park.</p>
    <p>Watch a ro­botic barista arm shake up your drinks, or rent a bar­be­cue pit for some out­door cook­ing.</p>
    <p>The Sun­day Times susses out five new cafes – each a des­ti­na­tion in it­self – to visit with the fam­ily.</p>
    <p>eu­niceq@sph.com.sg</p>
    <p>Fol­low The Straits Times Food on Face­book and In­sta­gram @strait­stimes­food</p>
    <p>Plan a dino day out – first to Changi Juras­sic Mile, then cool down at the pop-up Juras­sic World Cafe at Ion Sky.</p>
    <p>While there are no tow­er­ing di­nosaurs at the cafe that will draw gasps – the big­gest di­nosaur model is of ve­loci­rap­tor Blue from the Juras­sic World movies – there are still In­sta­gram spots and a small re­tail sec­tion for mer­chan­dise.</p>
    <p>At level 56 of the mall, you also get panoramic views of the city.</p>
    <p>The pop-up cafe’s de­but in Sin­ga­pore is a col­lab­o­ra­tion be­tween Ja­panese mall and depart­ment store op­er­a­tor Parco, Uni­ver­sal Brand Devel­op­ment, food and bev­er­age com­pany 1-Group, and Ion Or­chard.</p>
    <p>Menu op­tions in­clude a Juras­sic World Burger ($28), nasi lemak ($20) and a Christ­mas meat plat­ter ($25) with pork ribs.</p>
    <p>Hot drinks – such as the cap­puc­cino ($6), or matcha latte ($6.50) – come with dino latte de­signs. Or opt for the Milo ($9) drink – a take on the lo­cal Milo Di­nosaur bev­er­age.</p>
    <p>As with many themed cafes, food and drinks come at a pre­mium, but you get to keep a themed place­mat (with any food or­der) and a coaster (with any drink or­der) as sou­venirs.</p>

